notes.body_html:
Hello Sandhya,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

This email is with regards to your order #655846135892017152-60861, as checked your order was canceled on 06th December 2025. Due to some unforeseen circumstances, the order was not delivered to you by the expected date of delivery. We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

We would like to inform you that cancellation refund of Rs.2045.87/- initiated on 09th December 2025. The refund  will refunded  payments source within 05-07 business days.

We would request you to place a new order and we will ensure the order is delivered to you on priority.

Be rest assured as I have jotted down the details of your experience and PharmEasy will ensure all appropriate actions are taken to prevent similar situations from happening in the future. Looking forward to delighting you soon.

For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section. 

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards,
PharmEasy

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Hello PharmEasy Team,

I am raising a serious complaint regarding the blood sample collection for
my order *6238378*, completed today.

My scheduled collection time was *10:00 AM*, but the technician arrived
only around *10:20 AM*. Even before reaching, she was *asking for the OTP*,
which is unprofessional. After arriving late, she *pleaded with me to
change the collection time in the app*, saying she would receive a penalty
otherwise. Out of courtesy, I changed the time as she requested.

After the blood draw, I initially thought the pain was normal. Since the
area was covered with a bandage, I could not see any redness at that time.
However, as the day went on, the pain *continued to increase*, and by
evening it became *severe and unbearable*. When I removed the bandage, I
noticed the area had turned *red, swollen and bruised*.

? *I am attaching the images of the affected area for your reference.*

Additionally, I have *already informed your customer support through a
phone call*, but I have *not received any response, acknowledgement, or
follow-up* from your end. This lack of support in a health-related issue is
extremely disappointing.

This clearly indicates *negligence and poor technique* during sample
collection, along with unprofessional conduct.

I request the following actions:

   1.

   *Register this as an official complaint* and provide a complaint
   reference number.
   2.

   *Immediate action* against the technician for misconduct and improper
   procedure.
   3.

   *Compensation/refund* for the injury, pain, and inconvenience caused.
   4.

   Assurance that strict *quality, safety, and training protocols* are
   being followed by your technicians.
   5.

   An explanation for the *lack of response* despite my earlier phone
   complaint.

This is a serious issue affecting customer safety. I request an *urgent
response*.

Regards,
*Amalu Aravind A*
Phone: 7356871840
Order ID: *6238378*

--

helpdesk_ticket.subject: Urgent Complaint – Improper Sample Collection, Technician Misconduct & No Response (Order ID: 6238378)
helpdesk_ticket.description_html:
Hello PharmEasy Team,
I am raising a serious complaint regarding the blood sample collection for my order 6238378, completed today.
My scheduled collection time was 10:00 AM, but the technician arrived only around 10:20 AM. Even before reaching, she was asking for the OTP, which is unprofessional. After arriving late, she pleaded with me to change the collection time in the app, saying she would receive a penalty otherwise. Out of courtesy, I changed the time as she requested.
After the blood draw, I initially thought the pain was normal. Since the area was covered with a bandage, I could not see any redness at that time. However, as the day went on, the pain continued to increase, and by evening it became severe and unbearable. When I removed the bandage, I noticed the area had turned red, swollen and bruised.
👉 I am attaching the images of the affected area for your reference.
Additionally, I have already informed your customer support through a phone call, but I have not received any response, acknowledgement, or follow-up from your end. This lack of support in a health-related issue is extremely disappointing.
This clearly indicates negligence and poor technique during sample collection, along with unprofessional conduct.
I request the following actions:
  1. Register this as an official complaint and provide a complaint reference number.
  2. Immediate action against the technician for misconduct and improper procedure.
  3. Compensation/refund for the injury, pain, and inconvenience caused.
  4. Assurance that strict quality, safety, and training protocols are being followed by your technicians.
  5. An explanation for the lack of response despite my earlier phone complaint.
This is a serious issue affecting customer safety. I request an urgent response.
Regards,
Amalu Aravind A
Phone: 7356871840
Order ID: 6238378

notes.body: Hello Ayati,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     This email is with regards to your order #655989036145250304-84398, We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.     As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the LA SHIELD MAX SPF 80+ SUNSCREEN LOTION 50 GM   on 09th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.     Please note that the medicine will be collected within 24 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 48 business hours. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your bank account within 5-7 days.      We appreciate your patience in the meantime.     We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,  PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Ayati,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with regards to your order #655989036145250304-84398, We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the LA SHIELD MAX SPF 80+ SUNSCREEN LOTION 50 GM   on 09th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.
 
Please note that the medicine will be collected within 24 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 48 business hours. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your bank account within 5-7 days.
 
 We appreciate your patience in the meantime.
 
We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy
